SkyComment: Sky was partly cloudy but was able to to see some starts. Found the constellation Cygnus but was seen during Mag 3 conditions due to the street light. Street light bulb is actually an LED one and it emits more light that the standard street light bulb.
LocationComment: Street light chosen is one in a series of many on the street. The street lights are mostly a combination of the old-fashioned orange glow bulb and the new LED white light.

SkyComment: Sky was partly cloudy but was able to see the stars at Mag 3 conditions; constellation Cygnus was located using Globe at Night references.
LocationComment: Vertical light is one of two that are located at the bar establishment. Light emitted from the fixture is lower in power than the LED street light. There is a tree directly across from the light.

SkyComment: Constellation Cygnus was found using Globe At Night references. Sky is partly cloudy but was able to see stars during Mag 3 conditions.
LocationComment: Staircase lamp is located on the side of residence building. It is one of four lights that is situated on the first floor. All lights are identical but on different floors. Light bulbs are fluorescent. It emits a bright white light but not as bright as the LED street lamp. 50% of the light is blocked by the stair case and walls.

SkyComment: Constellation Cygnus was found using Globe at Night references. Sky was partly cloudy but was able to see the sky during Mag 4 conditions. The reason why it is Mag 4 is because the building lights are not strong enough to light the whole street/sky.
LocationComment: two lights located on the second floor and the entrance. The second floor light emits a stronger orange glow light that shines across the street. It uses some sort of orange flood light bulb.  The entrance light emits a softer glow that only reaches a foot away from the source of light. It uses a incandescent light bulb.    Combined the light emitted is at 50% and are the only lights on currently. The 3 street lights across the street (which are LED ) are off. The 2 building lights do not emit enough light for the street to be illuminated.
